commit.message:
Adapt SUSE Linux distributions to PRETTY_NAME -> NAME switch

SUSE Linux distributions do not use NAME like other distributions
do, and so we need to account for this.
Bump the script version to match released version

Add a fallback "generic guess" for DISTRIB_ID using NAME

Instead of using PRETTY_NAME, we can use NAME so that the identification
is more consistent, and we can produce some kind of reasonable fallback.

use printf to be more dash/posix shell compatible

The script is executed with bin/sh, if that isn't bash
then "echo -e" is not actually supported.

Fix syntax error, missing ;;

$ ./lsb_release
./lsb_release: line 204: syntax error near unexpected token `)'
./lsb_release: line 204: `              AlmaLinux*)'

Add basic support for some Red Hat distributions

redhat-lsb is not included in RHEL/CentOS 9, so in order to use this
as a substitute for lsb_release(1) formerly provided by redhat-lsb,
this adds some names to recognize and map to useful IDs.

Make script work with dash as /bin/sh.

`source` is non-portable, changed to `.`

Define Distribution ID based on PRETTY_NAME from /etc/os-release
Release version 3.1

Fix date of creation in manual page
Document /etc/os-release usage of lsb_release

Fix dependencies of manual page
Install "compat" links

Simplify a lot, remove all code for obsolete <distribution>-release
packages, we only use /etc/lsb_release and /etc/os-release
